<document> 

  <properties>
    <title>Launch analysis in cluster mode</title>
    <author email="jourdren@biologie.ens.fr">Laurent Jourdren</author> 
  </properties> 



  <body>
  
    <section name="Launch analysis in local mode">

      <p>This command launch Eoulsan in cluster mode. See the <a href="./clustermode.html">cluster mode configuration page</a>
         to see how to configure Eoulsan to handle the job scheduler of your cluster.</p>

      <ul>
         <li><b>Command name</b>: clusterexec</li>
         <li><b>Mandatory parameters</b>:
	<table>
		<tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Value</th><th>Description</th></tr>
		<tr><td>workflow file</td><td>a path</td><td>The workflow file to use</td></tr>
		<tr><td>design file</td><td>a path</td><td>The design file to use</td></tr>
	</table>
        </li>
	<br/>
         <li><b>Optional parameters</b>:
	<table>
		<tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Value</th><th>Description</th></tr>
		<tr><td>-d, --description</td><td>a string</td><td>The description of the analysis</td></tr>
	</table>
        </li>
	<br/>
        <li><b>Usage</b>:
<source>
$ eoulsan.sh clusterexec -d 'my first eoulsan launch on a cluster' workflow.xml design.txt
</source>

</li>
        
       </ul>
      
    </section>


  </body>
  
</document>
